  "name": "Arcane School Spirit",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/emerald_06.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You can talk up the power of your own school of magic to such an extent that creatures find it more difficult to resist your spells.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Bluff 1 rank, arcane school class feature, gnome.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>As a full-round action, you extol the virtues of your school of magic to one creature within 30 feet. Make a Bluff check opposed by a target's Sense Motive check; if you win the check, the target takes a -2 penalty on saving throws made to resist the next spell of this school that you cast. If your chosen school is universalist, choose a specific school each time you use this ability. If your Bluff check succeeds, however, your lack of true commitment to the school means the target takes only a -1 penalty on its saving throw.",
